      "content": "A humming AC unit can be quite unsettling, especially when the blades aren't spinning. It's possible that a loose belt or a misaligned pulley is causing the humming noise, rather than the fan blades themselves. You can try checking the belt tension and the pulley alignment to see if that resolves the issue. However, I wouldn't recommend going out there to investigate just yet, as you don't want to risk getting zapped by an exposed electrical component. It's better to wait until it's safe to do so, or consider calling a professional to take a look.",
